Some countries may try to protect their firms from exposure to the world market because they believe that this will help protect their economy from external competition and protect their citizens from being forced to sell their country's products or services abroad. Other countries may try to protect their firms from exposure to the world market because they believe that this will help them to become more competitive and innovative in the global marketplace.
